`aihub-refinement` failed in my CI run (https://cloud.cypress.io/projects/cfhedy/runs/11806/overview/199483ac-5530-44b1-b723-7d64cc47c04c/replay?att=1&roarHideRunsWithDiffGroupsAndTags=1&ts=1719624232918) with this error `did not expect this API to be called` when the extraction endpoint was called after the page was reloaded

@CJ @danny.lan the `PUT /extracted_fields` call looks correct and did succeed before the reload, so do we think this was a fluke? all 3 retries had this same error though
possibly something wrong then? will check
the `GET /extracted_fields` call after the reload also looks correct, so i’m not sure why the `/extraction` call was triggered at all…
i assume this is with danny's fix merged?
actually i don't think this is with danny's fix merged, this should've been fixed by https://github.com/instabase/instabase/pull/59362 i think
